'''''Byzantium after Byzantium''''' (''Bizanţ după Bizanţ'' in [[Romanian language|Romanian]]; ''Byzance après Byzance'' in French) is a 1935 book by the [[Romanian people|Romanian]] historian [[Nicolae Iorga]], which gave its name to a national cultural movement. It refers to the [[Byzantine Empire|Byzantine]] imperial influence on the political, social, cultural, and intellectual development of the principalities of [[Wallachia]] and [[Moldavia]]. The book deals with the impact of the fall of the [[Byzantine Empire]] on European civilization, the legacy and the continuation of Byzantine institutions and culture.

